<br>
2.  People that gank mobs from people that are engaging a mob can be reported.  Please do that, it's jacked up.<br>
<br>
3.  People that try gore twice and fail deserve to have someone else get a crack at it, IMO.  If you fail twice at nagafen at lower levels (at least on the bristlebane event calendar) you've already gone one more time than you should have.  Same thing here in my opinion.<br>
<br>
As I see it, manaburn can only be abused in a couple situations:<br>
<br>
-PvP.  This is definately messed up.  No one should get a 1 shot kill guarantee on most people.  Not PvP personally, but I see this as broken.<br>
<br>
-Ganking a mob out from someone.  Can't say I see a solution, but I hate that aspect too.  Jerks will be jerks, I suppose.<br>
<br>
That's all I see.  There may be more, but I haven't seen them.  Since &quot;Team Manaburn&quot; has come into play, I've had the option (though not the cash) to buy a green scale.  I do not belong to a guild, nor do I want to.  I like the freedom and lack of politics.  Before Team Manaburn came around, this was not even possible.  Similar situation with bards, more white scales have come to the market for those who do not want a guild or those who do not have the raiding power to take gore.<br>
<br>
I've personally never been affected negatively by Manaburn, and I plan on eventually getting my 52 wizard (rapidly approching my 55 warrior) manaburn if I ever get that high.<br>
<br>
I apologize to post a novel, I just tend to vent when I see misconceptions about a class, and people wanting to nerf another class for any reason.  Ask necros that played 2 years ago what the nerf stick feels like.<br>
<br>
Chaotic Conformity<br>
<br>
