- donalesque nerf, manaburn adds a buff (on mob) that cannot be overwritten.  That way you only have a MB every 30 seconds or whatever. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6318"><img src="http://www3.sympatico.ca/lchisholm/luth_sig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ueldryc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eldryc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/02 1:51:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=89>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Team Manaburn...blessing or Curse?</span><hr size=1> The claims that manaburn HELPS mid tier guilds are just plain laughable.  Is it so helpful when you're hoping to do Gore and Sev now that the uber guilds aren't too concerned with them, but you can't because team manaburn keeps smoking them instead?  Yeah, real helpful there... and yes, guilds do try to raid these mobs.  The main reason would be for the epic drops.  Well I bet they can buy it from some wizard for 100-200k.  Lucky them! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
