<br>
1. ..... My conclusion is that MB simply allows the kill of a mob like Gore or Sev to be faster, but with no less or more risk than 6 other similarly equipped and AA'd classes.<br>
<br>
6 Mana burn wizards each need 1778 mana to MB down a mob like Gore.   Now a level 60 wizard with only 1778 mana is extremly poorly equiped.  I would imagine most MB wizards have 2.5 - 3k (uber)  end of mana.   6 non-wizards who were equipped as well as a 1800 mana wizard could most definately NOT kill gorenaire.<br>
<br>
3. People that try gore twice and fail deserve to have someone else get a crack at it, IMO. If you fail twice at nagafen at lower levels (at least on the bristlebane event calendar) you've already gone one more time than you should have. <br>
<br>
I agree with this pretty much.  However,  my experience so far with the MB team is this:  While forming to try tallendor (for the first time) with my mid level guild, we failed at first because of underestimating Dragon Fear.  While we are rezzing for our second (and final try) of the night  (with about 5-10 more poeple incoming to help);  Team Manaburn of Terris Thule ports in on us.  While telling them we were going for tallendor a second time they setup in front of us and proceed to pull tallendor off of our druid who'd been keeping track of it while we rebuffed and ZOT him down.  No discussion, refusing to answer my tells.. just port and whack him.<br>
<br>
<br>
Manalow also said:<br>
Since &quot;Team Manaburn&quot; has come into play, I've had the option (though not the cash) to buy a green scale. I do not belong to a guild, nor do I want to. I like the freedom and lack of politics<br>
<br>
This is a VERY valid point and I do think your right.  But the very fact that these are on teh market for people with the plat, in some cases means, that guilds who are ready for this level of content  are being denied the experience.   I would also tend to argue that overall, the average firts time player climbing through the levels is very unlikely to get a shot at buying these items.  Most of the time its going to be some uber level player with spare cash who would like it for his twink.<br>
<br>
<br>
Overall I agree with the conclusion that Manaburn is a good thing.  Its a VERY useful tool for the mid level guild.   However,  I am firmly of the opinion that Team ManaBurn is NOT nor ever will be a good thing.  <br>
<br>
IF, the team MB went around and only knocked of dragons that were up for longer periods of time, i have no fault with that.  However,  when they are moving in on guilds actually attempting this content.. it just falls into the realm of being loot whores.    Seriously,  on TT i bet team MB gets 50 + percent of the MB targets if not more.   Why would they feel they needed to muscle on a night of what would have been great fun for our guild?    Only 2 outcomes of letting us have a second try would have happned:<br>
<br>
A)  We win on second turn, and the MB wizards would just lose 1 of MANY tallendors they would kill.   Also, losing to a big mob you've never beaten, recovering and winning is probably one of the best feelings you can get as a guild.  You get blown away, your recoup, revamp your strats and you win.   Its the best feeling in the world.  And Team MB now has the power to steal that from people, and from what i've seen proven over and over again they will do it.<br>
<br>
